TY  - JOUR
T1  - Commonalities in Reengineered Business Processes: Models and Issues
AU  - Buzacott, John A.
Y1  - 1996/05/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.42.5.768
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.42.5.768
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 768
EP  - 782
VL  - 42
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Process reengineering advocates making radical changes in how processing systems are structured, such as moving away from systems that use the principles of division of labor and division of management. Using formal system models from queueing theory, this paper explores the conditions under which such radical changes in system structure are likely to be appropriate. In general, a fairly high degree of variability in task times seems to be necessary.
